The design of the smilodon needs fixing. The shoulder hump of muscle is accurate, but the paws are too simple, the legs too short, the muscle definition absent, and the features on the face, including the fur around the cheeks, far too flat. When extended in jump, the legs don't extend past the snout. Just to the top left of volcano, there is foliage floating in the air, plus several other environmental glitches. I love your games, especially since the big maps and missions, I just wanted to give some constructive criticism. As I said in my review of the wolf sim, I'd LOVE to be a beta tester for these games, if you do that. I've been researching animals and ecology my whole life and feel I could take some of that research pressure off you. I'm off to play this new one some more now! After GFG reply: No problem, I totally understand about the keeping it on the low down. I saw an endless runner that stole your exact dragon design a few days ago. I'm glad you appreciate my suggestions. What about a penguin, hummingbird, bee, or butterfly sim? An animal with a different niche than the games you have made.
replyContent: Hey Melyssa! Thanks so much for the feedback, really good notes! Unfortunately we don't have a beta testers program right now, especially with the recent copycats popping up in the app store, they have forced us to be secretive about what we are working on. And btw thanks for calling those developers out, I read your other reviews!
